==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Huguenot
<hw>Hu"gue*not</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., properly a
dim. of <ets>Hugues</ets>. The name is probably derived from the
Christian name (<ets>Huguenot</ets>) of some person conspicuous as a
reformer.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A French Protestant of
the period of the religious wars in France in the 16th
century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huguenotism</ent>⟦br⟧
